The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Havells declares 1:1 bonus

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 Mumbai, May 18: Havells India Limited, the Delhi-based supplier of circuit-switching systems, today announced a bonus issue in the ratio of 1:1. The company also recommended a dividend of 50 per cent for financial year 2005-06.

 The record date for the issue of bonus shares will be decided after the annual general meeting on June 27, the company said in a statement to the stock exchange.

 The Havells board also approved the issue of foreign currency convertible bonds (FCCBs) up to a maximum of $60 million subject to the approval of shareholders. The company expects to fund its overseas acquisitions through the FCCB issue. 

 Havells net profit for the last financial year stood at Rs 63.2 crore on a turnover of Rs 1,115 crore. 




